{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n`run_git` (`src/rebar/_store/gitutil.py:26-61`) is characterized only through callers that\nmonkeypatch it (`tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_git_adapter_characterization.py:48-57`);\nthe real wrapper's own branches are never exercised directly. Signature:\n`run_git(cwd, *args, check=True, capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=None, env=None,\ninput_data=None)`. VALIDATED.\n\nSeparately, a latent contract hole was confirmed by direct probe: calling\n`run_git(..., input_data=b\"...\")` with the default `text=True` raises a confusing\n`AttributeError: 'bytes' object has no attribute 'encode'` from deep inside `subprocess`,\neven though the signature advertises `input_data: str | bytes | None`. The wrapper should\nturn this unsupported combination into a clear, actionable error rather than an opaque\nstdlib AttributeError.\n\n## What\n1. Add a focused contract test matrix in a NEW file `tests/unit/test_run_git_wrapper.py` that\n   invokes the REAL `run_git` (no monkeypatching of the wrapper) against a throwaway git repo\n   created in a tmp dir, asserting each documented branch (see AC).\n2. Narrow the `input_data` contract in `run_git`: when `input_data` is `bytes` and `text=True`\n   (the default), raise a clear `TypeError` naming the fix (binary stdin requires `text=False`),\n   instead of letting subprocess raise the opaque `AttributeError`. Update the docstring to\n   state the narrowed contract. `str` stdin with `text=True` (the only combination any current\n   caller uses) is unchanged.\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/_store/gitutil.py` — add the `bytes` + `text=True` guard in `run_git`; document it.\n- `tests/unit/test_run_git_wrapper.py` — new direct contract matrix.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `cwd=None` omits the `-C` prefix (argv starts `git <args>`); a path-like `cwd` inserts\n      `-C <cwd>` (argv starts `git -C <cwd> <args>`) — asserted by observing behavior against a\n      real repo (e.g. `rev-parse --show-toplevel` resolves to the given repo only when `-C` is\n      applied).\n- [ ] `check=True` on a failing git command raises `subprocess.CalledProcessError`; `check=False`\n      returns a `CompletedProcess` with the non-zero `returncode` instead.\n- [ ] `timeout` on a command that exceeds it propagates `subprocess.TimeoutExpired`.\n- [ ] `env` fully REPLACES the environment (a var present in the parent but absent from `env`\n      is not visible to git), asserted via a git command that reads an env var.\n- [ ] `input_data` (str) is forwarded to git's stdin (e.g. `hash-object --stdin` returns the\n      hash of the piped content).\n- [ ] `input_data=bytes` with `text=True` raises a clear `TypeError` (the narrowed contract),\n      NOT the opaque stdlib `AttributeError`; a test pins this behavior.\n- [ ] `make test` green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783794269974076001,"uuid":"4a005d4b-59f6-44b3-ac42-5a8d7d75d33d"}